## Queries

### Query Design

Queries select entities by component presence. Use inclusive (has all) and optional exclusive (has none) filters.

```cpp
// Entities with Position and Velocity, without Frozen
Query<Position, Velocity>.Exclude<Frozen>

// Entities with Health, optionally with Shield
Query<Health>.Optional<Shield>
```

### Query Performance

- [ ] Queries are cached; avoid creating queries per frame
- [ ] Iterate in archetype order to maximize cache hits
- [ ] Prefer sequential access over random access
- [ ] Batch process when possible (e.g., 64 entities at a time)

---

## Component Design

### Guidelines

| Guideline | Rationale |
|-----------|-----------|
| Components are data only | Enables SoA, cache efficiency |
| Keep components small | Better cache utilization |
| Avoid pointers in components | Breaks cache locality, complicates serialization |
| Use IDs to reference other entities | Enables archetype separation |
| No circular dependencies | Simplifies system order |

### Anti-Patterns

| Anti-Pattern | Problem | Correct Approach |
|--------------|---------|------------------|
| Logic in components | Defeats ECS benefits | Move to systems |
| Large heterogeneous components | Cache thrashing | Split into focused components |
| Components holding resources | Hard to relocate | Use resource handles (IDs) |
| Inheritance in components | Complicates queries | Composition via multiple components |

---

## World Management

### World Lifecycle

```
Create World -> Load Scene -> Spawn Entities -> Run Systems (loop) -> Unload Scene -> Destroy World
```

### Entity Creation

```cpp
Entity e = world.spawn();
world.add_component(e, Transform{0, 0, 0});
world.add_component(e, Velocity{1, 0, 0});
world.add_component(e, Health{100, 100});
```

### Entity Destruction

Defer destruction to avoid invalidating iterators during system execution.

```cpp
world.destroy_deferred(entity);
// Processed at end of frame
```

### Prefabs

Define entity templates for common configurations.

```yaml
prefab: enemy_soldier
components:
  - Transform
  - Velocity
  - Health: { current: 100, max: 100 }
  - AI: { behavior: patrol }
  - Collider: { radius: 0.5 }
```

---

## Checklist

Before implementing or refactoring ECS:

- [ ] Components are plain data structs
- [ ] Systems are stateless and operate on queries
- [ ] System order respects read/write dependencies
- [ ] Structural changes (add/remove component, destroy) are deferred
- [ ] Queries are cached, not created per frame
- [ ] No logic in components
- [ ] Entity references use IDs, not raw pointers
